
[1]polemical

   POLEM'ICAL, a. [Gr. war.]

   1. Controversial; disputative; intended to maintain an opinion or
   system in opposition to others; as a polemic treatise, discourse, essay
   or book; polemic divinity.

   2. Engaged in supporting an opinion or system by controversy; as a
   polemic writer.
